# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 5 — Mexico City bilingual routing
# /mexicocity        → mexicocity.html (Spanish default, served by Pages clean URL)
# /mexicocity/en     → mexicocity-en (English mirror, rewrite — URL stays clean)
# /mexicocity/*      → catch-all back to /mexicocity (legacy Squarespace subpaths)
#
# IMPORTANT: destination is /mexicocity-en (NO .html extension) per the
# Cloudflare Pages gotcha at the top of this file — including .html in the
# destination triggers Pages' auto-301 to the extensionless version, which
# bounces the user out of the rewrite (URL flips from /mexicocity/en to
# /mexicocity-en, EN nav button appears broken). Pages still resolves
# /mexicocity-en → mexicocity-en.html via pretty-URL lookup, so the actual
# file is served either way.
#
# Order matters: /en rule MUST sit above the catch-all.
# ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
/mexicocity/en  /mexicocity-en  200
/mexicocity/*   /mexicocity     301

